title: Concierge robbed at historic Annapolis hotel
text:
Concierge robbed at historic Annapolis hotel Governor Calvert House (Photo by Paul W. Gillespie - The Capital) 10/26/09 
A concierge was robbed Sunday night at Governor Calvert House on State Circle. 
A concierge was robbed Sunday night at Governor Calvert House on State Circle. ((Photo by Paul W. Gillespie - The Capital) 10/26/09) Concierge robbed at historic Annapolis hotel 
Annapolis police said the concierge of a historic Annapolis hotel was robbed Sunday night at gunpoint. 
At about 9:15 p.m., police said a man with his face covered enter the back of Governor Calvert House on State Circle, approached the concierge and displayed a handgun. The concierge, a 24-year-old man from Bowie, told police the suspect took his keys and attempted to remove money from behind the front desk. 
When the suspect was unsuccessful, he demanded the clerk give him money, police said. The concierge complied and the suspect fled out a back door, police said.
